However, this is only displayed for *JIRA System Administrators*, which may cause confusion. On [Finding New Add-ons|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/UPM/Finding+New+Add-ons] this is a bit more clear, but it has still mentioned:
bq. But while system administrators download and install add-ons through the Find new add-ons page, non-administrators use the page to request add-ons.
Which doesn't clarify in which view regular administrators fall under.

h3. Suggested Solution
Improve the documentation to clarify that only JIRA System Administrators will be able to view the requests and both regular administrators and non-administrator users can only requests the add-ons.

