h3. Summary
In *Service Desk* and *Software* projects on JIRA 7.0, adding the {{jira.issue.editable=false}} property to a step in the workflow only removes the "Edit" button, but allows for inline-editing of any field.

h3. Expected Behavior
The property should impede any editing from happening on issues from projects of any type.

h3. Actual Behavior
Inline-editing is allowed for any field on *Software* and *Service Desk* projects.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a *Software* or *Service Desk* project;
# Add the {{jira.issue.editable=false}} property to any step of the workflow used by that project, then publish the draft;
# Create an issue under that project and transition it to the status where that property was added;
# Notice it's possible to inline-edit any field;

h3. Workaround
Use the {{jira.permission.edit.denied}} property (with no value) instead. Set the value to *true* if no value doesn't work.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Cloud*. Using *JIRA Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRASERVER-45960].
  {panel}

h3. Current Behavior

When a JIRA import failed, the import is stuck with a blank page with the url {{https://<domain>.atlassian.net/secure/admin/StudioImport!finished.jspa}}

The logs are spammed with the following error if the import fails before importing the AO tables: 
{code}
2015-10-26 14:57:34.947872500 com.mysema.query.QueryException: Caught PSQLException for select "AO_54307E_SERVICEDESK"."ID", "AO_54307E_SERVICEDESK"."PROJECT_ID", "AO_54307E_SERVICEDESK"."DISABLED", "AO_54307E_SERVICEDESK"."PUBLIC_SIGNUP", "AO_54307E_SERVICEDESK"."OPEN_CUSTOMER_ACCESS", "AO_54307E_SERVICEDESK"."CREATED_BY_USER_KEY", "AO_54307E_SERVICEDESK"."CREATED_DATE", "AO_54307E_SERVICEDESK"."CREATED_WITH_EMPTY_PROJECT", "AO_54307E_SERVICEDESK"."VERSION_CREATED_AT", "AO_54307E_SERVICEDESK"."LEGACY_TRANSITION_DISABLED" from "AO_54307E_SERVICEDESK" "AO_54307E_SERVICEDESK" order by "AO_54307E_SERVICEDESK"."CREATED_DATE" 
{code}

This has causes confusion for the support team to troubleshoot and potentially spent more hours than they should.

h3. Feature Request
The import error should be handled better. There should be an error message in the UI to indicate any unfulfilled requirement instead of giving a blank screen.

The un-relevant error message should not be appearing.

